    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 3'>
      <repository-location derived-from='http://localhost:9100/workbooks/D210DataDashboardandStorytelling_17538989573670/Dashboard3?rev=' id='119682313' path='/workbooks/D210DataDashboardandStorytelling_17538989573670' revision='' />
      <style />
      <size maxheight='1315' maxwidth='1609' sizing-mode='range' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98616' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98928' x='536' y='692'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Demographics</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>Both datasets show similar gender distributions with slightly more females than males (CDC: </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>52% </run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>female, </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>48%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> male; WGU:</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> 51%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> female, </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>48%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> male, </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>1%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> nonbinary). Meanwhile, the age distributions are more contrasted, as the CDC data shows relatively even distribution across age groups while the WGU data has a significant spike in the &quot;80 or older&quot; category.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Condition KPIs</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Asthma:</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> More prevalent in the WGU data (</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>67.72%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>) vs the CDC (</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>32.38</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with WGU showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Diabetes:</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>Æ </run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>More prevalent in the WGU data (</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>66.12%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>) vs the CDC (</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>33.88</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with CDC data showing concentration in patients aged 65-74 and WGU showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Overweight:</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> Nearly even distribution between sources (CDC: </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>49.47%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>, WGU: </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>50.53%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with the CDC showing the most concentration in patients aged 50 to 74 and WGU showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Stroke:</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> Dramatically different (CDC: </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>16.65%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>, WGU: </run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>83.35%</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with WGU showing much higher prevalence across all age groups, but, as with the other three conditions, showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Takeaways</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>The heat maps reveal that WGU data consistently shows higher prevalence of conditions in older populations, while CDC data tends to show more even age distribution across conditions. That said, WGU&apos;s elderly-heavy population naturally drives higher prevalence of age-related conditions like stroke </run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>and diabetes, since these conditions disproportionately affect older adults.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>WGU appears to represent a geriatric or specialized elderly care population, while CDC likely represents a more general population sample. This may indicate that WGU should focus on incorporating appropriate treatment plans aligned with geriatric care and hiring geriatric specialists rather than expecting to apply the same level of preventative care across all age groups. </run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='52' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='84000' id='51' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='84000' x='8000' y='8000'>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98616' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98928' x='536' y='692'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Demographics</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>Both datasets show similar gender distributions with slightly more females than males (CDC: </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>52% </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>female, </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>48%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> male; WGU:</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> 51%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> female, </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>48%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> male, </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>1%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> nonbinary). Meanwhile, the age distributions are more contrasted, as the CDC data shows relatively even distribution across age groups while the WGU data has a significant spike in the &quot;80 or older&quot; category.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Condition KPIs</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Asthma:</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> More prevalent in the WGU data (</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>67.72%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>) vs the CDC (</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>32.38</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with WGU showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Diabetes:</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>Æ </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>More prevalent in the WGU data (</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>66.12%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>) vs the CDC (</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>33.88</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with CDC data showing concentration in patients aged 65-74 and WGU showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Overweight:</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> Nearly even distribution between sources (CDC: </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>49.47%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>, WGU: </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>50.53%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with the CDC showing the most concentration in patients aged 50 to 74 and WGU showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12' underline='true'>Stroke:</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'> Dramatically different (CDC: </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>16.65%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>, WGU: </run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>83.35%</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>), with WGU showing much higher prevalence across all age groups, but, as with the other three conditions, showing the greatest density in patients 80 or older.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Takeaways</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>The heat maps reveal that WGU data consistently shows higher prevalence of conditions in older populations, while CDC data tends to show more even age distribution across conditions. That said, WGU&apos;s elderly-heavy population naturally drives higher prevalence of age-related conditions like stroke </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>and diabetes, since these conditions disproportionately affect older adults.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontsize='12'>WGU appears to represent a geriatric or specialized elderly care population, while CDC likely represents a more general population sample. This may indicate that WGU should focus on incorporating appropriate treatment plans aligned with geriatric care and hiring geriatric specialists rather than expecting to apply the same level of preventative care across all age groups. </run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{02C128E5-EBF7-4299-AF3A-94C44FB76CA4}' />
    </dashboard>
    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Dashboard 4'>
      <repository-location derived-from='http://localhost:9100/workbooks/D210DataDashboardandStorytelling_17538989573670/Dashboard4?rev=' id='120645430' path='/workbooks/D210DataDashboardandStorytelling_17538989573670' revision='' />
      <style />
      <size maxheight='800' maxwidth='1000' minheight='800' minwidth='1000' />
      <zones>
        <zone h='100000' id='4' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
          <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
            <formatted-text>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Introduction</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>Æ                                     </run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>The following dashboards present medical data from two separate sources: Western Governors University (WGU) and the Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). The CDC data was collected as part of the Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System (BRFSS) survey in 2020. The BRFSS survey is the largest continuously conducted health survey system in the world, completing more than 400,000 adult interviews every year to assess the health status of U.S. residents across all 50 states as well as the District of Columbia and three U.S. territories.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>Æ   </run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Purpose</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>The purpose of this presentation is address the priorities of the Senior Vice President of Hospital Operations (SVP) by investigating patient outcome as a function of demographic factors. The CDC&apos;s BRFSS dataset enhances the insights that can be drawn from the WGU dataset by providing a benchmark against which to evaluate WGU&apos;s patient population. This comparison may highlight areas where WGU can implement targeted interventions to improve patient care.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>Æ   </run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Design</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>The first tab displays the demographic distributions of my two cleaned datasets. Two bar charts demonstrate the age category distribution for both the CDC and WGU data, while two pie charts show the gender distribution for each.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>The following section features heat maps for each condition across age categories for both data sources. A percentage occurrence chart is included for each pair of heat maps, showing the upper and lower limits for each range.  These heat maps visually highlight age-related trends in condition prevalence and can immediately indicate similarities and differences between trends at WGU and trends seen at the CDC level.</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>Three interactive filters (age category, gender, and data source) are embedded across all the data visualizations, empowering users to explore specific subgroups and compare them across datasets. </run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>Finally, all the dashboards are designed with colorblind limitations in mind, favoring contrasting blue and orange shades across visualizations to ensure broad visibility. </run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
              <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
            </formatted-text>
            <zone-style>
              <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
              <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
              <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
              <format attr='margin' value='4' />
            </zone-style>
          </zone>
          <zone-style>
            <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
            <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
            <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
            <format attr='margin' value='8' />
          </zone-style>
        </zone>
      </zones>
      <devicelayouts>
        <devicelayout auto-generated='true' name='Phone'>
          <size maxheight='700' minheight='700' sizing-mode='vscroll' />
          <zones>
            <zone h='100000' id='14' type-v2='layout-basic' w='100000' x='0' y='0'>
              <zone h='84000' id='13' param='vert' type-v2='layout-flow' w='84000' x='8000' y='8000'>
                <zone forceUpdate='true' h='98000' id='3' type-v2='text' w='98400' x='800' y='1000'>
                  <formatted-text>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Introduction</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>Æ                                     </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>The following dashboards present medical data from two separate sources: Western Governors University (WGU) and the Center for Disease Control and Prevention (CDC). The CDC data was collected as part of the Behavioral Risk Factor Surveillance System (BRFSS) survey in 2020. The BRFSS survey is the largest continuously conducted health survey system in the world, completing more than 400,000 adult interviews every year to assess the health status of U.S. residents across all 50 states as well as the District of Columbia and three U.S. territories.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>Æ   </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Purpose</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>The purpose of this presentation is address the priorities of the Senior Vice President of Hospital Operations (SVP) by investigating patient outcome as a function of demographic factors. The CDC&apos;s BRFSS dataset enhances the insights that can be drawn from the WGU dataset by providing a benchmark against which to evaluate WGU&apos;s patient population. This comparison may highlight areas where WGU can implement targeted interventions to improve patient care.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='12'>Æ   </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run bold='true' fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontsize='18' underline='true'>Design</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>The first tab displays the demographic distributions of my two cleaned datasets. Two bar charts demonstrate the age category distribution for both the CDC and WGU data, while two pie charts show the gender distribution for each.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>The following section features heat maps for each condition across age categories for both data sources. A percentage occurrence chart is included for each pair of heat maps, showing the upper and lower limits for each range.  These heat maps visually highlight age-related trends in condition prevalence and can immediately indicate similarities and differences between trends at WGU and trends seen at the CDC level.</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>Three interactive filters (age category, gender, and data source) are embedded across all the data visualizations, empowering users to explore specific subgroups and compare them across datasets. </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Tableau Book' fontsize='12'>Finally, all the dashboards are designed with colorblind limitations in mind, favoring contrasting blue and orange shades across visualizations to ensure broad visibility. </run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                    <run fontalignment='1'>Æ&#10;</run>
                  </formatted-text>
                  <zone-style>
                    <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                    <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                    <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                    <format attr='margin' value='4' />
                    <format attr='padding' value='0' />
                  </zone-style>
                </zone>
              </zone>
              <zone-style>
                <format attr='border-color' value='#000000' />
                <format attr='border-style' value='none' />
                <format attr='border-width' value='0' />
                <format attr='margin' value='8' />
              </zone-style>
            </zone>
          </zones>
        </devicelayout>
      </devicelayouts>
      <simple-id uuid='{790B049A-C584-4B6F-8EF7-F6BA53CC6CD4}' />
    </dashboard>
